{
  "texts": [
    "Examples of such devices include RFIDs, inexpensive smart cards (including wireless), wireless sensors, indicators, measuring devices, and custom controllers.",
    "Every lightweight block cipher creator must customize low-powered devices, balancing resource efficiency, performance (in throughput), and resistance to cryptographic attacks [43].",
    "See Fig. 6.",
    "In general, it is possible to effectively optimize any two out of the three objectives: security and low costs, security and execution, or low expenses and performance.",
    "However, it is tough to advance every one of the three structure objectives in the meantime."
  ]
}